dct_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Gosforth, solid, sheet 37
dct_description_sm: Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. (Third edition) Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 37 solid. Geological Survey of Great Britain. North Decimal Degree 54.483300. South Decimal Degree 54.3167. East Decimal Degree -3.3833. West Decimal Degree -3.8000. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of England (Third Edition). Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. Depths shown by contour intervals. "Published on one-inch quarter sheet 99 N.E. (Old Series) in 1891. Resurveyed in 1932 by T. Eastwood (District Geologist), F.M. Trotter (Senior Geologist), S.E.Hollingowrth, W.C.C. Rose (Geologists). Published 1937.".
dct_publisher_sm: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1937.
